{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=64533d985abaa4d2","title":"Maximo AI EAM Specialist","company":"MaxAccelerate","location":"{\"city\":\"Dubai\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Dubai\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Dubai\",\"latitude\":25.20485,\"longitude\":55.270782,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"4 months ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=64533d985abaa4d2","description":"Job Title: Maximo AI EAM Specialist\n\nLocation: Remote / Hybrid (Global Projects)\nCompany: MaxAccelerate\nDepartment: AI & Intelligent Asset Management Practice\nType: Full-Time / Contract\n\nAbout the Role\n\nMaxAccelerate is one of the market leaders in MAS 9 / MAS 9.1 AI deployments, with over 50+ successful installations supporting customers and partners worldwide. As we grow our AI practice, we are looking for an experienced Maximo AI EAM Specialist to help organisations transform their operations using the latest MAS-native AI, WatsonX, and DataMax AI capabilities.\n\nThis is a rare opportunity to work at the forefront of the AI-native Maximo era. You will support clients in deploying, understanding and scaling their AI infrastructure, enabling them to move from reactive to predictive operations within months.\n\nIf you are passionate about Maximo, reliability, data, and the future of AI in asset management — this is the role for you.\n\nKey ResponsibilitiesAI & MAS 9.1 Implementation\nLead or support deployment of MAS 9.1 AI Services including:\nMaximo Assistant (natural language interface)\nWork Order Intelligence (problem code & classification recommendations)\nFMEA Builder\nEmbedded WatsonX LLM & ML capabilities\nReliability and maintenance AI workflows\n\nConfigure AI features to align with customer business rules, asset structures and operating models.\nIntelligent Reporting & Data Architecture\nWork with Cognos 12 and DataMax AI to build:\nAI-driven dashboards\nKPI reporting\nPredictive maintenance views\nAsset health intelligence\nEnsure data readiness, integrity and AI model alignment across Maximo.\nAI Adoption & Use Case Delivery\nTransform customer business processes by embedding AI into:\nMaintenance planning\nWork order lifecycle\nFailure analysis\nReliability engineering\nAsset lifecycle management\nIdentify high-value AI use cases and guide customers through their first 90-day AI transformation.\nPartner Enablement & Customer Success\nSupport MaxAccelerate partners with AI readiness, architecture and rollout planning.\nTrain end-users, planners, engineers and executives on MAS 9.1 native AI + DataMax AI features.\nAssist clients in building an organisation-wide AI Operating Model.\n\nRequirements\n\nRequired ExperienceMaximo & MAS\n5+ years experience with Maximo / MAS 8 / MAS 9\nExcellent understanding of Maximo EAM modules including Work Management, Assets, Job Plans, Preventive Maintenance, Locations, Inventory, Procurement\nExperience with MAS 9.1 features is a major advantage\nAI & Reporting Technologies\nExperience with one or more of the following:\nWatsonX.ai (LLMs, data labelling, model governance)\nCognos 11/12\nAI/ML-based recommendations or predictive insights\nStrong data understanding (classifications, codes, data quality frameworks)\nSoft Skills\nPassion for AI and the future of intelligent asset management\nExcellent communication skills — ability to explain AI concepts to non-technical users\nStrong consulting and problem-solving capabilities\nAbility to work with both technical and business teams\n\nPreferred (Nice to Have)\nExperience with FMEA, RCA, and reliability engineering\nKnowledge of predictive maintenance or asset performance management\nExperience with Maximo upgrades, migrations or integrations\nExposure to DataMax AI or similar intelligence layers\nCertification in Maximo or WatsonX is a plus\n\nBenefits\n\nWhy Join MaxAccelerate?\nWork with the global market leader in MAS 9.1 AI transformation\nBe part of the team shaping the AI-native future of Maximo\nAccess world-class AI tools (WatsonX, DataMax AI, Cognos 12)\nDeliver high-impact, real-world AI solutions for major organisations\nSignificant career development in a fast-growing industry segment\nCompetitive salary + global project exposure"}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=65b83f3906e882f5","title":"Director Of Product Management","company":"ITCAN","location":"{\"city\":\"Dubai\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Dubai\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Dubai\",\"latitude\":25.20485,\"longitude\":55.270782,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"2 months ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=65b83f3906e882f5","description":"Role Summary\n\nWe are hiring a Director of Product Management to lead a portfolio of products and platform capabilities in a high-scale digital platform environment while also owning delivery leadership. You will set direction, drive outcomes, and build strong teams that ship with speed and quality. This role requires AI fluency and a track record of automating business operations to achieve scalability, reducing manual work, improving cycle times, and increasing operational reliability across the company.\n\nWhat You’ll Own\n\nProduct strategy and roadmap for a defined portfolio, tied to measurable outcomes.\n\nDelivery excellence across squads: planning, coordination, dependency management, and release readiness.\n\nAI-enabled initiatives across your portfolio, from discovery to measurable outcomes.\n\nOperational automation strategy for scalable execution across key business processes.\n\nKey Responsibilities\nStrategy & Portfolio Leadership:\n\nOwn product strategy across a defined portfolio, aligned to company priorities and customer value\n\n• Translate strategy into clear bets, sequencing, and measurable outcomes across growth, engagement, retention, monetization, and trust.\n\n• Lead quarterly planning and roadmap governance, balancing speed, quality, and long-term platform health.\n\n•Make principled trade-offs across customer experience, scalability, reliability, privacy, and cost-to-serve.\n\nAI-Enabled Product Leadership:\n\n• Identify and prioritize AI opportunities across the platform that deliver measurable customer and business impact.\n\n•Partner with Engineering and Data to shape AI-enabled initiatives into clear product requirements and delivery plans.\n\n• Ensure AI features are measurable and monitored post-launch, with clear success metrics and iteration loops.\n\nAutomation & Operational Scalability:\n\nIdentify high-friction operational workflows and lead automation initiatives that reduce manual effort and cost-to-serve.\n\nPartner with Operations, Finance, Support, and Engineering to map processes, define requirements, and deliver scalable automation.\n\nImprove throughput and reliability through workflow automation, integrations, and systemization of recurring processes.\n\nEstablish measurable targets for operational automation (cycle time, error rate, manual hours saved, SLA compliance) and drive continuous improvement.\n\nExecution & Delivery Leadership:\n\nLead the Delivery team to ensure predictable, high-quality execution across multiple squads.\n\nEstablish delivery standards and rituals: sprint and release planning, execution tracking, risk management, dependency mapping, and escalation paths.\n\nDrive cross-functional coordination across Engineering, Design, Data, and Operations to remove blockers early and keep teams moving.\n\nOwn release readiness and go-live processes, including phased rollouts and post-release retrospectives.\n\nProduct Craft & Decision Quality:\n\nSet the bar for product artifacts and delivery readiness: PRDs, acceptance criteria, rollout strategies, launch plans, and post-launch measurement.\n\nEnsure initiatives are instrumented and measurable, with clear baselines, targets, and monitoring.\n\nRaise the quality of prioritization by grounding decisions in evidence, customer insights, and business impact.\n\nPeople Leadership & Org Building\n\nLead, coach, and develop Product Managers and Delivery leads, including hiring, performance management, and career growth.\n\nBuild a culture of accountability, ownership, and delivery excellence, without sacrificing product quality.\n\nCreate consistency in how teams plan, execute, and communicate progress.\n\nStakeholder & Go-To-Market Leadership:\n\nServe as a senior partner to Marketing, Sales, Partnerships, and Customer teams to shape launches, positioning, and enablement.\n\nCommunicate product direction, progress, risks, and trade-offs with clarity to leadership and cross-functional partners.\n\nWhat Success Looks Like:\n\n• A roadmap that is understood, trusted, and tied to measurable outcomes.\n\n• Delivery becomes predictable: fewer surprises, clearer ownership, faster decision cycles, and healthier execution rhythms.\n\n• AI-enabled initiatives ship with measurable impact and improve through disciplined iteration.\n\n• Operational automation reduces manual effort, improves SLAs, and enables scale without linear headcount growth.\n\n• Core platform and product metrics improve consistently quarter over quarter.\n\nRequired Qualifications:\n\n8+ years of Product Management experience, with 3+ years leading Product Managers and/or delivery functions.\n\nRequired: experience building and scaling high-scale digital platforms, including high traffic environments, large event volumes, and complex cross-team dependencies.\n\nProven track record leading multi-team roadmaps and shipping customer-facing experiences and platform capabilities.\n\nRequired: AI fluency, with experience shipping AI-enabled product capabilities or leading teams delivering them in production environments.\n\nRequired: experience automating business operations to achieve scalability, including workflow automation, systems integrations, and reducing operational cost-to-serve.\n\nStrong product judgment with the ability to turn ambiguity into clear priorities and execution plans.\n\nStrong analytical mindset: metrics design, funnel and cohort thinking, experimentation literacy, and data-driven prioritization.\n\nStrong cross-functional leadership with Engineering and Design, including credibility in technical and UX trade-offs.\n\nExcellent communication and stakeholder management, including executive-ready updates and decision narratives.\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\nExperience in marketplace or multi-sided platforms.\n\nExperience scaling delivery operations across multiple squads (program management, release management, operational cadences).\n\nFamiliarity with modern experimentation and analytics stacks.\n\nExperience operating in privacy-sensitive environments.\nDepartment\nProduct Management\nLocations\nDubai\nRemote status\nFully Remote"}
