{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=80744f7d2cc0bb9c","title":"Head of Lead Generation (Kompetenza & Datamax AI)","company":"MaxAccelerate","location":"{\"city\":null,\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"UAE\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"UAE\",\"latitude\":0,\"longitude\":0,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"4 months ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=80744f7d2cc0bb9c","description":"The Role\n\nWe’re looking for a Head of Lead Generation — a hands-on growth specialist who can build and execute synchronized outbound strategies across multiple platforms and markets.\n\nThis role requires a strategic thinker with strong execution skills — someone who can design and manage multichannel outbound campaigns using Amplemarket, LinkedIn automation tools (HeyReach, Aimfox), and Salesforce, while continuously testing, refining, and optimizing for maximum ROI.\n\nRequirements\n\nKey Responsibilities\nDevelop and execute the lead generation strategy for Kompetenza and Datamax AI, aligning with business goals and sales targets.\nBuild and manage outbound sequences across Amplemarket, LinkedIn automation tools (HeyReach & Aimfox), and Salesforce — ensuring synchronization across all systems.\nConduct A/B testing on messaging, targeting, and outreach frequency to optimize conversion rates.\nMaintain and manage CRM workflows inside Salesforce, ensuring all leads, activities, and campaigns are tracked accurately.\nPartner with leadership to brainstorm and implement creative, out-of-the-box ideas for outbound growth, including new verticals, partner outreach, and webinars.\nManage campaign analytics and performance dashboards to report KPIs and ROI.\nCoordinate with the sales team to hand off qualified leads and ensure follow-up consistency.\nContinuously research and test new automation and AI tools to improve lead efficiency and scalability.\nPlan and coordinate monthly webinars and lead-gen events to drive partner and client engagement.\n\nRequirements\n4+ years of experience in B2B lead generation, outbound marketing, or growth automation, ideally within SaaS, tech, or consulting.\nHands-on experience with Amplemarket, LinkedIn automation (HeyReach, Aimfox, etc.), and Salesforce CRM.\nProven ability to build and manage automated multichannel prospecting workflows.\nData-driven mindset with experience in A/B testing and campaign analytics.\nExcellent written and verbal communication skills.\nStrategic thinker with a “test and learn” attitude — unafraid to experiment and iterate fast.\nStrong organizational skills; able to manage campaigns for multiple brands simultaneously (Kompetenza & Datamax AI).\n\nNice to Have\nExperience running webinars or partner campaigns for lead generation.\nFamiliarity with AI-powered sales tools and workflow automation.\nPrevious exposure to Salesforce AppExchange solutions or CRM-driven B2B SaaS.\n\nBenefits\n\nWhat We Offer\nOpportunity to shape the growth engine of two innovative AI-first companies.\nFreedom to experiment, test ideas, and build automation-first strategies.\nCollaborative team culture working directly with executive leadership.\nCompetitive compensation with performance-based incentives.\nRemote-first work culture and the freedom to experiment with ideas."}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=80dcbd7738580a20","title":"SEO Content Operator (AI-First) — Ranking Nerd / SEO Genius (Dubai / Remote)","company":"MM INTERNATIONAL TRADING FZCO","location":"{\"city\":\"Dubai\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Dubai\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Dubai\",\"latitude\":25.20485,\"longitude\":55.270782,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"3 months ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=80dcbd7738580a20","description":"*What this role is*\n\nWe are *not* looking for a “content writer” and not for a generic “SEO consultant”.\n\nWe are looking for a *SEO Content Operator* who can build an AI-driven content + ranking machine that:\n\n* dominates Google in high-intent keywords\n* improves visibility in AI search (ChatGPT / Perplexity etc.)\n* generates consistent high-ticket leads\n\nIf your skill is only “writing nice articles” → not a fit.\nIf you can build rankings and systems → welcome.\n\n*Your Mission*\n\nBuild and run a consistent SEO production engine for two websites:\n\n*Crypto Currency Mining*\n\n* Create *Money Pages* (hosting, buying miners, category pages, location pages)\n* Create *Support Content* (comparisons, guides, profitability, FAQs)\n* Build internal linking + update existing pages\n\n*Licenseplate (UAE):*\n\n* Create Money Pages (2-digit / 3-digit, emirates, buying process, guides)\n* Create Q&A/FAQ content + topic clusters that rank\n\nYou will not be measured by word count.\nYou will be measured by:\n✅ rankings\n✅ output per week\n✅ organic leads / inquiries\n\n*What you will do (operational tasks)*\n\n* Keyword + SERP analysis (understand search intent)\n* Build topic clusters + site structure\n* Produce Money Pages + blog content (AI-first, human-edited)\n* Optimize for snippets (H-tags, FAQs, structure)\n* Build internal linking strategically\n* Update and improve existing pages\n* Publish inside our CMS (Gambio / WordPress / custom)\n\n*What you must have*\n\n* Proven SEO results (show proof)\n* You work AI-first (ChatGPT / Claude / Perplexity, etc.)\n* Fast execution + consistency\n* Operator mindset: *plan → publish → measure → improve*\n\n*Nice to have (not required):*\n\n* Mining / hosting knowledge\n* High-ticket lead-gen experience\n* Basic technical SEO understanding\n\n*Salary*\n\nFixed salary + performance bonus (based on skill level)\nSerious candidates provide their expected salary.\n\n*How to Apply (IMPORTANT)*\n\nNo generic applications.\n\n*Only applications that answer the required questions below will be reviewed.*\n\nJob Type: Full-time\n\nPay: From AED12,000.00 per month\n\n\n\nApplication Question(s):\n* 1) Proof of results\nShare 1 URL (or a screenshot) of a website/page you ranked.\nWhich keywords? What positions? In what timeframe?\n* 2) Your AI + SEO production workflow\nHow do you produce 10–30 SEO pages per week using AI without sounding like AI?\nBe specific (process, editing, structure).\n* 3) Money Page vs Blog Post\nExplain the difference between a Money Page and a Blog Post with one example from:\nA) Bitcoin mining / ASIC hosting OR\nB) Dubai license plates\nWhich would you build first and why?\n* 4) 30-day mini case\nYou have 30 days to maximize organic leads.\nName your Top 5 pages you would build first for:\nA) MillionMiner\nB) licenseplate.ae\nTitles/slugs are enough. No long text.\n* 5) Tools you actually use\nList the tools you actively use (examples: Google Search Console, Ahrefs/Semrush, Screaming Frog, Surfer, etc.)"}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=83b1f539511cac52","title":"Health Insurance Advisor","company":"InsuranceMarket.ae™","location":"{\"city\":\"Remote\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Remote\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Remote\",\"latitude\":25,\"longitude\":-40,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":true,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"2 months ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=83b1f539511cac52","description":"Remote WorkFull-Time\n\nDepartment: Retail Medical Department\nReports To: Chief Business Development Officer\n\nAbout InsuranceMarket.ae\n\nInsuranceMarket.ae is the UAE’s leading and most trusted insurance brokerage, recognized for its customer-first approach, digital innovation, and over 30 years of market excellence.\n\nAs part of our expanding Health Insurance division, we are seeking experienced and performance-driven Advisors to handle inbound health insurance inquiries and convert qualified leads into new business.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\n1. Inbound Lead Conversion\n\nHandle inbound health insurance inquiries generated through online platforms, digital campaigns, and referrals.\nConduct consultative discussions to assess customer needs and recommend suitable health insurance plans compliant with DoH, DHA, and MOH regulations.\nPresent accurate and transparent quotations, ensuring clients fully understand coverage options, benefits, and exclusions.\nAchieve and exceed monthly and quarterly new business targets through high-quality lead conversion.\nMaintain professionalism, empathy, and solution-oriented communication throughout the sales cycle.\n\n2. Customer Experience & Relationship Management\n\nProvide a premium advisory experience from initial inquiry to policy activation.\nEnsure all interactions are clear, compliant, and customer-centric.\nDeliver post-sale support, confirming policy details, documentation accuracy, and activation completion.\nBuild strong relationships with new clients to enhance retention and future cross-sell opportunities.\n\n3. Compliance & Operational Excellence\n\nEnsure full adherence to Central Bank of UAE and Health Authority compliance standards.\nAccurately record all leads, quotations, and client communications within the CRM system.\nCoordinate with underwriting and operations teams to ensure efficient policy processing and issue resolution.\nFollow internal quality and data protection standards at all times.\nDesired Skills & Qualifications\n\nEducation & Experience\n\nBachelor’s degree from a reputed university (mandatory).\nMinimum 2–3 years of proven success in health insurance sales, specifically in managing and converting inbound leads within the UAE market.\nDemonstrated achievement of sales targets and strong performance consistency.\nGood understanding of UAE health insurance regulations and policy frameworks.\n\nTechnical & Soft Skills\n\nExcellent English communication skills (verbal and written); additional languages are an advantage.\nStrong consultative selling, negotiation, and closing skills.\nProficiency with CRM systems, quotation tools, and digital communication platforms.\nHighly organized, detail-oriented, and able to manage multiple client interactions efficiently.\nSelf-motivated and target-driven, with strong follow-up discipline and time management.\n\nPersonality Traits\n\nConfident, empathetic, and professional communicator.\nResilient and goal-oriented, thriving in a fast-paced, target-driven environment.\nTeam player with integrity, adaptability, and a commitment to continuous improvement.\nWork Parameters:\n\nWork Schedule:\n\nMonday to Friday: 8:00 AM – 5:30 PM GST or 9:00 AM – 6:30 PM GST\nSaturday: 9:00 AM – 1:00 PM GST\n\nWork Type: Remote\n\nWhy Join Us?\nBe part of a trusted, award-winning brand in the UAE insurance industry.\n100% inbound leads — no cold calling required.\nCompetitive incentive structure with uncapped potential.\nAccess to qualified, high-intent leads from our digital platforms.\nComprehensive training and ongoing professional development."}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=87d5922248eb571c","title":"Technical Lead (Rust)","company":"Keyrock","location":"{\"city\":\"Abu Dhabi\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Abu Dhabi\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Abu Dhabi\",\"latitude\":24.46,\"longitude\":54.36,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"2 months ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=87d5922248eb571c","description":"About Keyrock\n\nSince our beginnings in 2017, we've grown to be a leading change-maker in the digital asset space, renowned for our partnerships and innovation.\n\nToday, we rock with over 180 team members around the world. Our diverse team hails from 42 nationalities, with backgrounds ranging from DeFi natives to PhDs. Predominantly remote, we have hubs in London, Brussels and Singapore, and host regular online and offline hangouts to keep the crew tight.\n\nWe are trading on more than 80 exchanges, and working with a wide array of asset issuers. As a well-established market maker, our distinctive expertise led us to expand rapidly. Today, our services span market making, options trading, high-frequency trading, OTC, and DeFi trading desks.\n\nBut we’re more than a service provider. We’re an initiator. We're pioneers in adopting the Rust development language for our algorithmic trading, and champions of its use in the industry. We support the growth of Web3 startups through our Accelerator Program. We upgrade ecosystems by injecting liquidity into promising DeFi, RWA, and NFT protocols. And we push the industry's progress with our research and governance initiatives.\n\nAt Keyrock, we're not just envisioning the future of digital assets. We're actively building it.\n\nMission statement\n\nThe Tech Lead plays a pivotal role in bridging business objectives with technical execution. This role is not purely managerial nor solely individual contributor, but a hybrid position that combines hands-on engineering, architectural leadership, and team enablement. A Tech Lead ensures delivery excellence by actively contributing to the codebase, guiding the team technically, and aligning execution with long-term strategic goals.\n\nAt Keyrock, the Tech Lead is a senior technical contributor who drives the implementation and delivery of engineering initiatives within their Business Unit. The Tech Lead is accountable for technical execution and delivery quality, ensuring that systems are built to high standards of reliability, performance, and maintainability.\n\nWhile the Head of Engineering (HoE) focuses on strategic alignment - ensuring that engineering outcomes meet the broader objectives agreed with the Head of Product (HoP) - the Tech Lead operates as the executional deputy, translating those strategic objectives into code, architecture, and delivery outcomes.\n\nJob Description\n\nAct as the technical point of accountability for the Service Market Making Business Unit.\n\nBalance strategic thinking with pragmatic delivery, ensuring systems are built to last while meeting immediate needs.\n\nChampion collaboration across teams, ensuring alignment between product, design, QA, and engineering.\n\nInspire and develop engineers through mentorship, coaching, and technical guidance, fostering growth and autonomy within the team.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\nDrive Delivery and Alignment: Partner with the Head of Engineering to own delivery of entire work-streams, ensuring architecture and engineering decisions align with both immediate requirements and business strategy.\n\nBalance Code and Leadership: Contribute directly through coding, while also focusing on architecture design, peer reviews, and cross-functional communication.\n\nMentor and Elevate Engineers: Provide structured feedback through design and code reviews, support skill development, and empower junior and mid-level engineers to take ownership.\n\nTechnical Leadership: Guide system design, ensure scalability and resilience, and optimise performance across applications and infrastructure.\n\nMaintain Standards: Uphold engineering best practices, enforce coding guidelines, and partner with QA to embed automation and validation in the delivery pipeline.\n\nCodebase Health: Manage technical debt, lead refactoring initiatives, and ensure long-term maintainability and operational excellence.\n\nCross-Functional Collaboration: Work closely with product managers, designers, and QA engineers to define scope, refine requirements, and plan delivery in a transparent and predictable manner.\n\nRisk Management: Anticipate technical risks, dependencies, and trade-offs early, and propose mitigations to safeguard delivery timelines.\n\nRequirements\n\nBachelor’s or Master’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering or a related discipline, or equivalent practical experience\n\n5+ years in a Technical Leadership position guiding teams, shaping architecture, and driving delivery of complex projects\n\nDemonstrated expertise in architecting and maintaining high-concurrency, low-latency trading systems at scale\n\nAdvanced proficiency in Rust; working knowledge of Node.js (JavaScript/TypeScript) and Python is an advantage\n\nDeep experience with data-intensive architectures and real-time data pipelines\n\nProven track record deploying, optimising and operating AWS environments for ultra-low-latency workloads\n\nHands-on experience containerising applications and managing Kubernetes clusters in production\n\nFamiliarity with GitOps workflows to automate infrastructure provisioning, configuration and deployments\n\nSolid command of software engineering best practices, including Agile methodologies, DevOps principles and end-to-end CI/CD pipelines\n\nKnowledge of DevSecFinOps principles to embed security, compliance and cost-governance throughout the delivery lifecycle\n\nDemonstrated leadership of engineering teams, with a commitment to fostering collaboration, mentorship and continuous professional growth\n\nExcellent communication and stakeholder-management skills, able to partner effectively with Product, Architecture, Quantitative Research and Operations\n\nStrong analytical and problem-solving mindset, with a passion for building scalable, reliable and secure systems\n\nDeep domain knowledge of finance and trading, particularly within the cryptocurrency sector\n\nExperience in fast-paced, dynamic financial or fintech environments is highly desirable\n\nWe would like the successful candidate to be based in the UK or Europe. Remote and flexible work options are available.\n\nSoft Skills & Competencies\n\nOwnership & Reliability – Take full responsibility for your work. Deliver high-quality service, meet deadlines, and follow through on commitments. Anticipate and proactively address potential issues before they arise.\n\nInitiative & Problem-Solving – Approach challenges with a problem-solving entrepreneurial mindset. Make sound, independent judgments and take the initiative to drive solutions rather than waiting for instructions.\n\nOperational Diligence – Respond strategically to technical and operational challenges, ensuring robust and reliable trading infrastructure while instilling confidence in the team’s processes.\n\nCuriosity & Growth Mindset – Continuously seek to improve your technical skills and knowledge. Stay ahead of industry trends and take the initiative to practice and explore new technologies that excite you.\n\nExcellent Communication Skills with a team player mindset, collaborating within a fully remote global team.\n\nWe would like the successful candidate to be based in the UK or Europe. Remote and flexible work options are available.\n\nOur recruitment philosophy\n\nWe value self-awareness in our recruitment process. We seek people who understand themselves and their career goals. We're after those with the right skills and a conscious choice to join our field. The perfect fit? A crypto enthusiast who’s driven, collaborative, and delivers solid, scalable outcomes.\n\nOur offer\n\nA competitive salary package, with various benefits depending on the method of engagement (employee or freelancer).\n\nAutonomy in your time management thanks to flexible working hours and the opportunity to work remotely\n\nThe freedom to create your own entrepreneurial experience by being part of a team of people in search of excellence\n\nAs an employer we are committed to build an inclusive, diverse and non-discriminating work environment. We welcome employees of all backgrounds, ethnicities, genders, creed and sexual orientation. We hire, reward and promote entirely based on merit and performance.\n\nDue to the nature of our business and external requirements, we perform background checks on all potential employees, passing which is a prerequisite to join Keyrock.\n\nhttps://keyrock.com/careers/"}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=87ff3c71f8745a34","title":"Content Manager for AboFlah (Remote or Dubai-based)","company":"8Flamez","location":"{\"city\":\"Dubai\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Dubai\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Dubai\",\"latitude\":25.20485,\"longitude\":55.270782,\"streetAddress\":\"8FLAMEZ HQ,Dubai,United Arab Emirates\",\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"2 months ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=87ff3c71f8745a34","description":"Work with AboFlah: The Middle East's biggest YouTuber\n\n8Flamez is looking for a sharp, organized, creativity obsessed Content Manager to lead and streamline the production machine behind AboFlah’s videos.\n\nThis isn’t just any content role, it’s about managing the heartbeat of one of the region’s most influential channels. You’ll oversee the creative team that brings AboFlah’s ideas to life, make sure every deadline is hit, keep quality sky high, and ensure his feedback is executed with precision. If you live and breathe YouTube, thrive under pressure, and know how to get the best out of a remote team, this is your moment.\n\nWe are a lean, elite crew operating at creator scale. We want someone who brings structure, calm, and leadership to a fast moving creative ecosystem.\n\n8Flamez تبحث عن مدير محتوى شديد الذكاء، منظم، ومهووس بالإبداع لقيادة وتنظيم منظومة الإنتاج وراء فيديوهات أبو فلة.\n\nهذا ليس دوراً عادياً في صناعة المحتوى، بل هو مسؤولية إدارة نبض واحد من أكثر القنوات تأثيراً في المنطقة. ستكون مسؤولاً عن فريق الإبداع الذي يحول أفكار أبو فلة إلى واقع، تضمن الالتزام بكل المواعيد، تحافظ على أعلى مستويات الجودة، وتتأكد من تنفيذ ملاحظاته بدقة كاملة. إذا كنت تعيش وتتنفس يوتيوب، وتجيد العمل تحت الضغط، وتعرف كيف تستخرج أفضل ما لدى فريق يعمل عن بعد، فهذه فرصتك.\n\nنحن فريق صغير ومحترف يعمل بمعايير صناع المحتوى الكبار. نبحث عن شخص يجلب الهيكلة، والهدوء، والقيادة إلى منظومة إبداعية تتحرك بسرعة.\n\nWhat will you do?\nOwn the Content Pipeline: Oversee every stage of video production from concept to upload. Keep the team aligned, the tasks clear, and the workflow smooth.\nManage the Creative Team: Lead editors, thumbnail designers, producers and researchers. Set expectations, give clear direction, and keep the team motivated and accountable.\nHandle Feedback Flow: Review AboFlah’s notes, share them clearly with the team, and make sure revisions are done correctly and on time.\nProtect Deadlines: Build schedules, enforce timelines, and remove blockers so videos are always delivered when they should be.\nMaintain Quality Control: Check creative outputs for consistency, storytelling strength, pacing, and alignment with AboFlah’s style.\nImprove Processes: Identify weak points in the workflow and upgrade them. Introduce tools, templates and systems that make the team faster and sharper.\nBridge Communication: Act as the central point of communication between AboFlah and the production team so everyone stays aligned.\n\nامتلك خط إنتاج المحتوى: أشرف على كل مرحلة من مراحل إنتاج الفيديو من الفكرة حتى الرفع. حافظ على انسجام الفريق، وضوح المهام، وسلاسة سير العمل.\n\nأدر الفريق الإبداعي: قد المحررين، ومصممي الصور المصغرة، والمنتجين، والباحثين. ضع التوقعات، وقدم توجيهاً واضحاً، وحافظ على تحفيز الفريق ومحاسبته.\n\nأدار تدفق الملاحظات: راجع ملاحظات أبو فلة، وشاركها بوضوح مع الفريق، وتأكد من تنفيذ التعديلات بشكل صحيح وفي الوقت المحدد.\n\nحمِ المواعيد النهائية: أنشئ الجداول، وطبق الخطط الزمنية، وأزل العقبات حتى يتم تسليم الفيديوهات في وقتها.\n\nحافظ على ضبط الجودة: راجع المخرجات الإبداعية للتأكد من الاتساق، وقوة السرد، والإيقاع الصحيح، وملائمة أسلوب أبو فلة.\n\nحسن العمليات: اكتشف نقاط الضعف في سير العمل وطورها. أدخل أدوات، وقوالب، وأنظمة تجعل الفريق أسرع وأكثر دقة.\n\nاربط قنوات التواصل: كن نقطة الاتصال المركزية بين أبو فلة وفريق الإنتاج حتى يبقى الجميع على نفس المسار.\n\nHave you got what it takes?\n\nExperience in content or production management. You have led creative teams before, ideally with YouTube creators or digital content brands.\nDeep understanding of YouTube culture and creator workflows.\nExcellent communicator. You can be kind, firm, clear, and assertive with a remote team.\nHighly organized. Systems and structure are your best friends.\nAble to work Dubai based or remotely.\nComfortable giving direction and making decisions fast in a high stakes environment.\nReady to start as soon as possible.\n\nخبرة في إدارة المحتوى أو الإنتاج. لديك خبرة في قيادة فرق إبداعية من قبل، ويفضل أن تكون مع صناع محتوى يوتيوب أو علامات المحتوى الرقمي.\n\nفهم عميق لثقافة يوتيوب وآليات عمل صناع المحتوى.\n\nمهارات تواصل ممتازة. يمكنك أن تكون لطيفاً وحازماً وواضحاً وقادراً على توجيه فريق يعمل عن بعد.\n\nشديد التنظيم. الأنظمة والبنية هي نقطة قوتك.\n\nقادر على العمل من دبي أو عن بعد.\n\nمرتاح في إعطاء التوجيه واتخاذ القرارات بسرعة في بيئة مليئة بالضغوط.\n\nجاهز للبدء في أقرب وقت ممكن."}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=8aad231a5a426536","title":"Forward Deployed Engineer - International (CENTCOM AOR)","company":"NODA AI","location":"{\"city\":null,\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"UAE\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"UAE\",\"latitude\":0,\"longitude\":0,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"6 days ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=8aad231a5a426536","description":"Forward Deployed Engineer – CENTCOM AOR\n\nLocation: UAE (CENTCOM AOR) (Home office: Austin, TX)\n\nTravel: Mission-dependent, up to ~75% (OCONUS rotations)\nClearance Requirement: Active Secret required\n\nAbout NODA\n\nNODA is a veteran-owned, venture-backed technology company transforming how unmanned systems collaborate in complex, mission-critical environments. Our distributed orchestration platform enables autonomous coordination of heterogeneous unmanned systems across air, sea, land, and space with vital applications in defense, intelligence, and commercial sectors.\n\nOur Forward Deployed Engineers are the technical tip of the spear in theater — the hands-on integration and fielding specialists who stand up NODA’s orchestration platform on DoD networks and partner platforms at forward locations. They operate directly alongside deployed warfighters, translating mission requirements into working capability under operational timelines and real-world constraints.\n\nThe Role\n\nAs a Forward Deployed Engineer – Customer Solutions, you are the technical owner of delivery and customer success in the field. You deploy, integrate, and operationalize NODA systems on DoD networks and partner platforms — working directly with operators to ensure mission success under real-world conditions.\n\nWhile much of your time is spent on integration and fielding in theater, you also contribute to the core platform — building shared libraries, reusable integration components, and deployment tooling that accelerate future engagements. You are the direct link between deployed operator needs and platform development.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\n- Deploy and integrate systems on NIPR, SIPR, and mission partner networks\n- Build adapters and integration layers connecting our orchestration platform to autonomous vehicle control protocols and APIs (MAVLink, REST, C2 systems such as ATAK/TAK Server)\n- Own end-to-end delivery: install integrate validate operational handoff\n- Operate and troubleshoot in DDIL and RF-constrained environments\n- Debug across networking, software, and hardware boundaries\n- Train operators and ensure adoption and mission readiness\n- Support scoping and technical planning for new in-theater engagements\n- Build shared libraries and reusable components that accelerate future deployments\n- Develop deployment tooling and automation for secure, constrained, and disconnected environments\n- Translate field feedback into actionable engineering improvements and funnel product requirements back to core teams\n\nRequired Qualifications\n\n- 3+ years of software or systems engineering experience building integrations, APIs, or distributed systems\n- Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, Electrical Engineering, Robotics, or related field (or equivalent hands-on experience)\n- Strong proficiency in Python and/or C++\n- Linux and networking experience (TCP/IP, UDP, debugging, remote system administration)\n- Experience integrating with external APIs, protocols, or hardware systems\n- Active Secret clearance and U.S. citizenship\n- Valid U.S. passport (12+ months validity, multiple blank pages) and willingness to deploy OCONUS for extended rotations (up to 30–120 days)\n- Ability to operate independently in austere environments with limited supervision and connectivity\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n- Experience with DoD networks (NIPR/SIPR) and accreditation processes (RMF, ATO, STIG compliance)\n- Familiarity with MAVLink, ROS/ROS2, C2 systems, or autonomy platforms\n- Experience with autonomous systems, robotics, or unmanned vehicles (UAS, UGV, USV, UUV)\n- DevSecOps experience deploying software in secure, constrained, or classified environments\n- Experience in RF/DDIL environments or tactical communications systems (ATAK, TAK Server, Link 16)\n- Experience with embedded systems, microcontrollers, firmware interfaces, or sensor integration (cameras, LIDAR, radar, EO/IR)\n- Knowledge of ML model deployment and inference optimization\n- Working knowledge of ITAR/EAR, Foreign Disclosure, and export control practices\n- Familiarity with DoD installation access procedures, CAC sponsorship, LOAs, and country clearance (APACS)\n- Prior military service or OCONUS deployment experience\n- Existing TS/SCI clearance\n\nSkills & Attributes\n\n- Technical ownership: takes end-to-end accountability for integration and fielding outcomes in theater, from initial setup through operator handoff.\n- Systems thinker: reasons across software, networking, and hardware boundaries to diagnose and resolve issues in complex, multi-system environments.\n- Field-ready: operates effectively in austere, high-tempo conditions with limited reach-back, constrained connectivity, and an 8–10 hour time difference from headquarters.\n- Operator-focused: translates between engineering and operational language; earns the trust of warfighters by delivering working capability, not just functional software.\n- Platform contributor: treats field learnings as first-class inputs to the core platform — documents integration patterns, files product requirements, and builds reusable components that outlast the deployment.\n- Startup discipline: combines the adaptability of a startup engineer with the documentation rigor required to hand off to military users and sustain capability after departure.\n\nWhat We Offer\n\n- Deployment uplifts and per diem during in-theater operations\n- Company-covered travel, lodging, and logistics support for rotations\n- Flexible time off with rest cycles between rotations\n- Federal holidays\n- Comprehensive health, dental, and vision benefits\n- Free One Medical membership\n- 401(k)\n\nGrowth Path at NODA\n\nFDE Senior FDE Lead FDE (International) Mission Lead / Product / Core Engineering\n\nWe are an Equal Opportunity Employer and welcome applicants from all backgrounds. All qualified individuals will receive consideration for employment regardless of race, age, color, religion, sex, national origin, disability, or protected veteran status."}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=90e2980259ab2c54","title":"Global Alliance Manager - Strategic Accounts","company":"LockThreat","location":"{\"city\":null,\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"UAE\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"UAE\",\"latitude\":0,\"longitude\":0,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"4 months ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=90e2980259ab2c54","description":"Company Background\n\nLockThreat LLC is a forward-thinking technology company specializing in Enterprise Governance, Risk, and Compliance (GRC) automation. Our AI-powered platform helps organizations streamline compliance, cybersecurity, and risk management operations across industries and regulatory environments. By centralizing GRC processes and delivering real-time insights, LockThreat enables businesses to reduce risk, simplify compliance reporting, and enhance operational resilience in highly regulated markets. (https://www.lockthreat.ai/)\n\nFounded to provide intuitive, secure, and data-driven GRC solutions, LockThreat partners closely with its clients, offering continuous support, training, and insights to help organizations transform compliance from a requirement into a strategic advantage. Headquartered in Alpharetta, Georgia, LockThreat serves diverse industries including financial services, healthcare, retail, telecommunications, energy, and government sectors and supports compliance with hundreds of frameworks and global standards. The company is rapidly expanding globally through strategic partnerships, collaborations with major cloud providers, and participation in leading cybersecurity and risk events, positioning LockThreat as a trusted enterprise GRC partner in over 10 countries.\n\nAs an early-stage company, we are highly focused on:\n\nCapital-efficient growth\nClear ICP definition\nRepeatable GTM motions\nStrategic partnerships that materially accelerate enterprise adoption\n\nGlobal Systems Integrators (GSIs) and Global Consulting Firms are a force multiplier, not just a GTM channel.\n\nRole Summary\n\nThe Global Alliance Manager – Strategic Accounts is responsible for designing, launching, and scaling a small number of deep, high-impact global alliances with Tier-1 GSIs and Global Consulting Firms.\n\nThis is a hands-on builder role, not a caretaker role. You will define what “good” looks like for global alliances at a Series A company—then operationalize it.\n\nYou will own:\n\nGlobal partner strategy – Strategic Accounts\nExecutive alignment\nJoint solution positioning\nPartner-led pipeline creation\nEarly proof points that justify long-term investment\n\nWhat You’ll Do\n\nGlobal Alliance Strategy & Program Design\n\nIdentify and prioritize 3–5 global strategic alliance targets based on:\nICP overlap\nServices-led leverage\nGlobal account reach\nGRC practice maturity\nDesign a Series A–appropriate global alliance model, including:\nPartner segmentation and tiers\nEngagement rules\nGlobal vs regional ownership model\nBuild 12–24 month joint business plans (JBPs) with clear assumptions, milestones, and success criteria.\n\nRevenue & Pipeline Creation (Primary Accountability)\n\nDrive partner-sourced and partner-influenced enterprise pipeline across global accounts.\nFocus on fewer, higher-quality opportunities rather than broad activation.\nPartner closely with LockThreat leadership on:\nOverall Account strategy\nExecutive mapping\nDeal Shaping and Delivery\nMulti-country pursuit coordination& Enablement Optimzation\nEnforce disciplined qualification using MEDDIC / MEDDPICCR to protect scarce Series A resources.\n\nExecutive Alignment & Relationship Management\n\nEstablish executive-level relationships with:\nGlobal alliance leaders\nGRC / risk / cyber service line leaders\nRegional managing partners\nLead:\nExecutive briefings\nAlliance steering committees\nQBRs focused on outcomes, not activity\nPosition the company as a value-driven, outcome- oriented partner that enables scalable solutions and services that drive differentiation—not a niche tool.\n\nSolution & Services Co-Creation\n\nAlign product capabilities to partner consulting and managed services offerings.\nSupport development of:\nPartner-delivered GRC accelerators\nIndustry-specific compliance solutions\nRepeatable implementation patterns\nEnsure services-led motions reinforce product adoption, expansion, and stickiness.\n\nInternal Operating Rhythm\n\nAct as the internal voice of strategic alliances across Product, Sales, Marketing, and Customer Success.\nBuild lightweight but effective alliance operating processes:\nPipeline inspection\nForecast accuracy\nProduct & Engineering enhancements\nExecutive escalation paths\nMaintain clean, auditable data in CRM.\n\nIdeal Partner Profile\n\nTier-1 GSIs and Global Consulting Firms\nEstablished global GRC, risk, audit, cybersecurity, or transformation practices\nStrong enterprise presence across all industries, beneficial focus areas of Financial Services, Energy, Healthcare, & Government\nExperience delivering multi-country, multi-year programs\n\nRequirements\n\nRequired Experience & Qualifications\n\n8+ years in enterprise sales, alliances, or strategic partnerships\n5+ years managing global or multi-region strategic accounts\nDemonstrated success working with GSIs or global consulting firms\nStrong understanding of services-led GTM motions\nBackground in GRC, cybersecurity, enterprise SaaS, or risk platforms\nComfortable building programs from scratch with minimal structure\nExecutive-level communication and negotiation skills\nCRM fluency (Salesforce, HubSpot, Zoho)\nExceptional Business Acumen and problem-solving skills\nExcellent writing skills and capability to build own GTM Assets\nAbility to collaborate cross-functionally at every level in the organization\nHigh Ownership Mindset and the ability to managed multiple initiatives at once\nExcellent Presentation skills, capable of delivering level 1 & 2 solution demos\nFlexibility to work alternative hours (Global Time Zone)\nAbility and willingness to travel, up to 50% of time.\n\nWhat sets you apart\n\n· You’ve worked in an early-stage environment where you had to figure things out without a perfect playbook\n\n· You truly understand the cybersecurity or GRC buyer and related sales motion\n\n· You’re equally comfortable speaking with an Auditor or GRC Analyst, as you are selling to the CEO or Managing Director.\n\n· You can take complex environments and define conceptual solutions to deliver desired outcomes.\n\nBenefits\n\nWhat You Can Expect From LockThreat\n\nWe're building a company where different perspectives aren't just accepted; they're essential to solving hard problems. We're committed to creating an environment where you can do your best work while being your authentic self.\n\nWe support our team through:\n\nCompetitive compensation\nComprehensive health, dental, and vision coverage\nFlexible PTO and paid holidays\nProfessional development budget and growth opportunities\nRemote-friendly work environment\nPaid parental leave\nThe autonomy to build programs and make real impact from day one\n\nWe're committed to building a diverse and inclusive organization and are proud to be an equal opportunity employer. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment without regard to race, color, religion, gender, gender identity or expression, sexual orientation, national origin, genetics, pregnancy, disability, age, veteran status, or other dimensions of identity."}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=90f9857d8ff36531","title":"Lead Security Engineer (AI Security, DeFi, Self Custody)","company":"Binance","location":"{\"city\":\"Dubai\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Dubai\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Dubai\",\"latitude\":25.20485,\"longitude\":55.270782,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"a month ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=90f9857d8ff36531","description":"Binance is a leading global blockchain ecosystem behind the world’s largest cryptocurrency exchange by trading volume and registered users. We are trusted by 300+ million people in 100+ countries for our industry-leading security, user fund transparency, trading engine speed, deep liquidity, and an unmatched portfolio of digital-asset products. Binance offerings range from trading and finance to education, research, payments, institutional services, Web3 features, and more. We leverage the power of digital assets and blockchain to build an inclusive financial ecosystem to advance the freedom of money and improve financial access for people around the world.\n\nWe are looking for a proactive and solutions-oriented Lead Security Engineer who drives progress by enabling secure innovation and solutions. This candidate will work closely with cross-functional teams to move the needle forward in a secure and efficient way—finding practical, effective security solutions that empower the business while protecting critical assets.\n\nThis role is 100% Remote, Work from Home.\nResponsibilities\nLeverage deep cybersecurity knowledge across DeFi domains—such as blockchain, smart contracts and wallet protection—alongside application security, system security, and cryptographic techniques.\nLead hands-on implementation of IT Security Risk Management and collaborate with stakeholders to protect assets, data, and systems.\nOversee cyber threat and vulnerability management, including penetration testing coordination.\nLead security incident response and management with timely escalation.\nConduct security risk assessments for projects and third-party integrations.\nEnsure compliance with security governance, regulatory, and internal policies.\nDefine and lead AI security strategy and governance, including safe adoption of LLMs across products and internal workflows, with clear policies for data handling, prompt safety, and third-party integrations.\nDesign and enforce controls for AI-specific threats (prompt injection, data leakage, model abuse), while embedding secure AI practices into SDLC and engineering platforms.\nDrive AI-enabled security operations, leveraging automation and AI to improve threat detection, triage, and response efficiency.\nRequirements\n2+ years of self-custody wallet experience\n10+ years of cybersecurity experience in international, regulated environments.\nStrong leadership combined with deep technical expertise.\nActive contributor to the security community.\nExperience in global, fast-paced, multicultural teams.\nBachelor’s degree or higher in IT, Cybersecurity, or related field.\nHands-on experience managing cybersecurity operations and best practices.\nKnowledge of frameworks such as NIST, ISO 27001/27701, CIS, and PCI-DSS.\nExcellent communication skills and a collaborative mindset.\nPassionate about emerging cybersecurity trends and threats.\nWhy Binance\n• Shape the future with the world’s leading blockchain ecosystem\n• Collaborate with world-class talent in a user-centric global organization with a flat structure\n• Tackle unique, fast-paced projects with autonomy in an innovative environment\n• Thrive in a results-driven workplace with opportunities for career growth and continuous learning\n• Competitive salary and company benefits\n• Work-from-home arrangement (the arrangement may vary depending on the work nature of the business team)\n\nBinance is committed to being an equal opportunity employer. We believe that having a diverse workforce is fundamental to our success.\nBy submitting a job application, you confirm that you have read and agree to our Candidate Privacy Notice.\n\nWe may use artificial intelligence (AI) tools to support parts of the hiring process, such as reviewing applications, analyzing resumes, or assessing responses. These tools assist our recruitment team but do not replace human judgment. Final hiring decisions are ultimately made by humans. If you would like more information about how your data is processed, please contact us."}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=91c29d72aa44a621","title":"Creative Project Manager","company":"Soar With Us","location":"{\"city\":\"Dubai\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Dubai\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Dubai\",\"latitude\":25.20485,\"longitude\":55.270782,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"13 days ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=91c29d72aa44a621","description":"Creative Project Manager\nDepartment: Account Management | Creative Asset Management\nReports to: Senior Account Manager\nLocation: Remote\nCompensation: £1400 - £2000 (B2B Contract)\n\nAbout Soar Group\n\nThe Soar Group is a UK performance agency group comprising three specialist agencies. With over 100M in ad spend under management and a team of 100+, we work with 7-9 figure DTC and e-commerce brands across Meta, TikTok, and Google.\n\nWe were nominated for Meta's Creative Diversity Award 2025 and are recognised as the UK's #1 independent Meta agency group. Our creative department is the group's biggest growth lever - and this role is central to where it goes next.\n\nOur values: Extreme Ownership. Radical Curiosity. Kind Candour. Outcome Obsessed.\n\nThe Role\n\nWe're looking for a highly organised and proactive Project Manager to join our Account Management team. As a PM at Hambi, you're the operational backbone of every campaign - ensuring assets move on time, nothing falls through the cracks, and our Account Managers stay focused on strategy and client relationships.\n\nYou'll be embedded across multiple client accounts, managing the full delivery lifecycle from brand onboarding through to final creative output. This is a detail-obsessed, communication-first role for someone who thrives on keeping complex moving parts in order.\n\nRequirements\n\nWhat You'll Own\n\nUGC coordination - own the end-to-end UGC process across all assigned accounts, from creator briefing and onboarding through to content review and delivery\nProduction coordination - manage shoot logistics and production timelines, acting as the operational link between the Account lead and the Production team\nCampaign onboarding - be briefed on each account alongside the AM, understand the brand deeply, and confirm campaign timelines before kickoff\nAsset tracking - own and maintain accurate, real-time content schedules across all accounts; the tracker should always reflect live delivery status\nInternal communication - keep Account Managers proactively updated; flag risks early and ensure nothing catches the AM off guard\nUGC and influencer communication - maintain strong relationships with creators and influencers, ensuring smooth processes, consistent deliveries, and a high return-rate\nQuality control - review assets before they reach the AM and catch issues early, not late\n\nA day-to-day in the life of a PM\n\nYou start each day reviewing content schedules across all assigned accounts - chasing anything overdue, flagging risks to the AM before they become problems. Creator comms, content QC, and tracker updates run throughout the day. Nothing waits until tomorrow.\n\nAccount onboarding - attend the AM briefing, receive the onboarding form, confirm campaign timelines, and join the internal kick-off call\nCampaign activation - attend kickoffs and commercial briefings as new campaigns go live; brief creators and the production team simultaneously from day one\nUGC delivery - Send out UGC briefs, and run Day 3 and Day 5 chasers on live UGC, QC content before it reaches the AM, and manage end-to-end creator delivery\nProduction - confirm shortlists and shoot plans with the AM, coordinate logistics with the production team, and attend pre-production meetings\nWeekly wrap - send each AM a clean overview every Friday so nothing is ever a surprise\n\nWhat We're Looking For\n\n2+ years in a project management, operations, or production coordination role - agency experience is a strong advantage\nExceptional organisational skills and attention to detail - you notice what others miss\nA proactive, solutions-first mindset - you flag problems before they become escalations and bring a fix, not just a flag\nStrong, clear communication — reliable, concise, and always one step ahead\nComfortable managing multiple accounts and stakeholders simultaneously without dropping the ball\nFamiliarity with UGC, content production, or performance creative workflows is a big plus\n\nBenefits\n\nWhat You'll Get\n\nReal ownership from day one - you run your accounts, not just assist on them\nA fast-paced, creative environment where your work directly impacts campaign performance\nClear career progression within a growing agency that is scaling quickly\nA collaborative, high-performance team that values output, clarity, and moving fast"}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=91f770bf00ae34dd","title":"Process & Systems Enablement Specialist","company":"ITCAN","location":"{\"city\":\"Dubai\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Dubai\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Dubai\",\"latitude\":25.20485,\"longitude\":55.270782,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"a month ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=91f770bf00ae34dd","description":"About the Role\n\nAs a Process & Systems Enablement Specialist, you will design, document and operationalise repeatable processes and the systems that support them. Working across Product, Engineering, Operations and Commercial teams, you will simplify complex workflows, reduce manual work, and ensure teams have reliable tools, clear procedures and the data they need to operate at scale. This is a hands-on role that combines process design, systems configuration, integration work and cross-functional change management.\n\nKey Responsibilities\n\nMap, document and optimise end-to-end operational workflows across multiple products and platforms, identifying automation opportunities and failure modes.\n\nConfigure and maintain internal systems and tooling (CRM, ticketing, workflow orchestration, admin panels and integrations) to support streamlined operations.\n\nDesign and implement integrations and automations using APIs, webhooks, ETL/ELT patterns and third-party platforms to reduce manual handoffs and data reconciliation.\n\nCreate clear, scalable process documentation, runbooks and SOPs so teams can operate independently and consistently.\n\nAuthor tracking and instrumentation requirements to ensure operational observability: logs, metrics, alerts and dashboards for key process health indicators.\n\nPartner with Engineering and Product to prioritise system improvements, scope development work and validate that releases meet operational needs and reliability standards.\n\nLead change management and training for new processes and systems, including stakeholder communication, onboarding materials and hands-on support during rollouts.\n\nOwn incident playbooks and contribute to incident response readiness: triage steps, escalation paths and post-incident reviews with actionable remediation plans.\n\nMaintain data quality and access controls across operational systems, ensuring privacy-sensitive information is handled according to policy.\n\nContinuously measure process performance and iterate: reduce cycle times, error rates and manual interventions through disciplined experimentation and monitoring.\n\nHow You’ll Do It\n\nDevelop clear process maps, decision trees and acceptance criteria that translate business workflows into system requirements.\n\nImplement and maintain integrations using standard patterns (webhooks, message queues, scheduled jobs) and document failure/retry behaviours.\n\nBuild and maintain dashboards and alerts for operational KPIs, and perform routine QA to detect regressions or instrumentation gaps.\n\nCreate and maintain runbooks and training materials; run workshops and drop-in clinics to increase adoption and reduce support load.\n\nCollaborate with technical and non-technical stakeholders to scope deliverables, set success metrics and verify post-deployment outcomes.\n\nRequirements\n\n3+ years’ experience in operations, business systems, process improvement or a related role supporting cross-functional teams.\n\nPractical experience with business systems such as CRMs, ticketing/workflow tools, analytics platforms and common SaaS integrations.\n\nWorking knowledge of integration patterns (APIs, webhooks, ETL/ELT, event-driven architectures) and a pragmatic approach to automation.\n\nStrong documentation skills — able to produce unambiguous process specs, runbooks and training guides that scale across teams.\n\nSolid analytical skills with experience instrumenting and monitoring processes using metrics, dashboards and alerts.\n\nExcellent stakeholder management and communication skills with the ability to translate between technical and business audiences.\n\nComfortable working in fast-paced environments and taking ownership of cross-functional initiatives from discovery through to operational handover.\n\nNice to Have\n\nExperience with workflow orchestration platforms, low-code automation tools, or integration platforms (Zapier, Make, Workato, n8n, or similar).\n\nFamiliarity with SQL or basic scripting (Python, Google Apps Script) to build small automations and perform data validation.\n\nExposure to observability and monitoring stacks (Datadog, Grafana, Looker/Looker Studio or similar) for operational metrics and alerting.\n\nExperience designing processes in privacy-conscious environments and implementing appropriate access controls.\n\nPrevious experience leading cross-functional change programmes or training initiatives.\n\nWhat Success Looks Like\n\nOperational workflows are well-documented, measurable and reliably executed with minimal manual intervention.\n\nSystems and integrations reduce cycle times and error rates, and internal teams trust the tools and runbooks provided.\n\nIncidents are resolved according to playbooks, root causes are addressed, and recurrence is demonstrably reduced.\n\nProcess and system improvements are delivered iteratively with clear metrics demonstrating impact on scalability and efficiency.\n\nWhy Join Us?\n\nYou’ll join a collaborative team where your work directly improves how the business operates at scale. This role offers exposure to multiple product lines, the chance to shape tooling and process standards, and the opportunity to make measurable impact by reducing operational complexity and enabling teams to move faster.\nDepartment\nKnowledge Management\nRemote status\nFully Remote"}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=954ad11076badf03","title":"BD Executive","company":"Dizzaract FZ LLC","location":"{\"city\":\"Remote\",\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"Remote\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"Remote\",\"latitude\":25,\"longitude\":-40,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":true,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"8 days ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=954ad11076badf03","description":"Full Org Path: Business Development Department\n\nCompensation: is discussed individually with each candidate based on experience.\n\n*About Dizzaract*\n\nDizzaract is a UAE-based game development studio founded in 2022, headquartered at Yas Creative Hub, Abu Dhabi. We develop cutting-edge AI-powered games and systems, including our innovation R&D laboratory FAR labs, the upcoming hero shooter Farcana, and the AI gaming identity platform GAMED. Our research and development team boasts over 100 peer-reviewed papers and more than 20 patents in AI-driven gameplay, digital ownership, and competitive design. With a diverse team of more than 80 professionals from over 20 countries, we are committed to innovation, excellence, and building a culture that drives performance and results.\n\n*Role Summary*\n\nWe are seeking a *Senior BD Executive* who lives and breathes the AI ecosystem. with deep expertise in AI models, inference, and MLOps commercialization. You won’t just be managing a pipeline; you will be leveraging your deep industry roots to open doors that others can’t. Your goal is to position FAR AI as the go-to inference solution for AI startups, scale-ups and engineering/dev teams globally.\n\n*Key Responsibilities*\n\n*Key Responsibilities*\n\n*1. Hunt & Close B2B Inference Deals*\n\n* Leverage your existing network of AI/ML decision-makers to open doors at AI startups, scale-ups, and enterprise engineering teams.\n* Own the full sales cycle for FAR AI inference: prospecting, technical scoping, negotiation, and closing.\n* Drive Monthly Recurring Revenue (MRR) through API subscriptions, licensing, and revenue-share agreements.\n\n*2. Monetize AI Inference & Models*\n\n* Translate technical value (latency, throughput, cost-per-inference, token pricing) into clear commercial propositions.\n* Package FAR Labs' proprietary models and R&D output (20+ patents) into sellable products for gaming, media, and security clients.\n* Partner with engineering to define pricing strategies and structure deals that maximize gross margin per inference.\n\n3. Market Intelligence & Positioning\n\n* Track the competitive inference landscape (AWS Bedrock, Azure AI, Replicate, open-source) and identify where FAR AI wins on latency, cost, or domain specialization.\n* Feed market signals back to R&D to shape product direction.\n\n4. Client & Technical Engagement\n\n* Act as the bridge between clients and ML engineers — scoping POCs, supporting API integration, and validating performance against SLAs.\n\n5. Pipeline Ownership & Reporting\n\n* Own BD KPIs: active partnerships, MRR, CAC, and deal velocity.\n* Report directly to the COO and Director of BD on pipeline, forecasts, and strategic accounts.\n\n*Required Qualifications & Skills*\n\n* Proven Track Record: 3-5 years of experience in high-growth B2B sales, specifically within Cloud Infrastructure (IaaS), SaaS or AI hardware/software.\n* Deep AI Network: An active, \"warm\" network of decision-makers in the AI/ML ecosystem.\n* Technical Fluency: Deep understanding of the inference stack—concepts such as Token-per-second, KV caching, quantization and GPU cluster orchestration.\n* The \"Hunter\" Mindset: A relentless drive to close deals in a fast-paced, ambiguous environment where speed is a competitive advantage.\n* Familiarity with AI deployment tools: Hugging Face, TensorRT, vLLM, or cloud inference endpoints is a strong plus.\n* Excellent negotiation, communication, and presentation skills for technical and non-technical audiences.\n* Self-starter mindset, comfortable with remote work and fast-paced R&D environments.\n\n*Final Note*\n\nThis role is for a business-savvy AI expert who wants to turn cutting-edge research into real revenue. You will have direct access to 20+ patents, a world-class R&D team, and an emerging AI ecosystem in Abu Dhabi. If you understand inference pricing models, can sell APIs to developers and enterprises, and want to shape the commercial future of AI in gaming — this is your opportunity.\n\n\n\nApplication Question(s):\n* How many years have you spent selling AI/ML, cloud infrastructure (IaaS), or API-based developer products in a B2B context?\n* Describe the largest deal you've personally closed. Include: deal size (ARR or TCV), sales cycle length, and whether the relationship was inbound, outbound, or from your existing network.\n* Which of the following have you personally sold or closed deals around? (Select all that apply):\n\n- LLM APIs or inference endpoints\n- Cloud GPU/compute infrastructure\n- AI/ML platforms or MLOps tools\n- Traditional SaaS (CRM, HR, marketing tools)\n- Gaming technology or middleware\n- None of the above\n* Name 3-5 companies in the AI/ML ecosystem where you have existing warm relationships with decision-makers. You don't need to name the individuals — just the companies and the seniority of your contact(VP Engineering, Head of AI, CTO, or technical founders).\n* If we gave you your first 30 days, which 3 companies would you approach first to sell FAR AI inference into, and why those specifically?\n\nWork Location: Remote"}
{"source":"indeed","source_id":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=95c4034f0653800f","title":"Sales Development Representative, SMB | Benelux","company":"DEEL","location":"{\"city\":null,\"postalCode\":null,\"country\":\"UAE\",\"countryCode\":\"AE\",\"formattedAddressLong\":\"UAE\",\"formattedAddressShort\":\"UAE\",\"latitude\":0,\"longitude\":0,\"streetAddress\":null,\"fullAddress\":null}","remote":false,"salary":"{}","posted_at":"8 months ago","url":"https://www.indeed.com/viewjob?jk=95c4034f0653800f","description":"Who we are is what we do.\n\nDeel is the all-in-one payroll and HR platform for global teams. Our vision is to unlock global opportunity for every person, team, and business. Built for the way the world works today, Deel combines HRIS, payroll, compliance, benefits, performance, and equipment management into one seamless platform. With AI-powered tools and a fully owned payroll infrastructure, Deel supports every worker type in 150+ countries—helping businesses scale smarter, faster, and more compliantly.\n\nAmong the largest globally distributed companies in the world, our team of 7,000 spans more than 100 countries, speaks 74 languages, and brings a connected and dynamic culture that drives continuous learning and innovation for our customers.\n\nWhy should you be part of our success story?\n\nAs the fastest-growing Software as a Service (SaaS) company in history, Deel is transforming how global talent connects with world-class companies – breaking down borders that have traditionally limited both hiring and career opportunities. We're not just building software; we're creating the infrastructure for the future of work, enabling a more diverse and inclusive global economy. In 2024 alone, we paid $11.2 billion to workers in nearly 100 currencies and provided healthcare and benefits to workers in 109 countries—ensuring people get paid and protected, no matter where they are.\n\nOur momentum is reflected in our achievements and customer satisfaction: CNBC Disruptor 50, Forbes Cloud 100, Deloitte Fast 500, and repeated recognition on Y Combinator’s top companies list – all while maintaining a 4.83 average rating from 15,000 reviews across G2, Trustpilot, Captera, Apple and Google.\n\nYour experience at Deel will be a career accelerator. At the forefront of the global work revolution, you'll tackle complex challenges that impact millions of people's working lives. With our momentum—backed by a $17.3 billion valuation and $1 B in Annual Recurring Revenue (ARR) in just over five years—you'll drive meaningful impact while building expertise that makes you a sought-after leader in the transformation of global work.\n\nSummary\n\nAs our SDR, SMB you'll be playing a crucial role of breaking into new accounts and fostering relationships with multiple contacts within all levels of our target customer segments. You understand the impact that you'll create to the bottom line, playing one of the most vital roles in the company. The day-to-day role includes collaboration with the wider sales team, market research to identify new potential customers and leads, and qualification of these leads by learning about their approach to onboarding.\n\nResponsibilities\n\nGenerate new business opportunities through outbound prospecting, including email, phone, and social media outreach\n\nIdentify and qualify prospective clients by understanding their needs and challenges\n\nSchedule product demonstrations for qualified prospects with Account Executives\n\nCollaborate with the sales and marketing teams to improve lead generation strategies\n\nConsistently achieve monthly and quarterly targets for qualified meetings and pipeline generation\n\nMaintain accurate and up-to-date records in our CRM system\n\nParticipate in regular sales training and professional development opportunities\n\nQualifications\n\n1-2 years of experience in a sales development or similar outbound commercial role\n\nExceptional communication and interpersonal skills\n\nAbility to work in a fast-paced, dynamic, and remote team environment\n\nStrong organizational and time management skills\n\nSelf-motivated, results-driven, and eager to learn\n\nAbility to work autonomously and self source solutions\n\nProven track record of achieving and exceeding targets in a quota-carrying role\n\nExperience with CRM systems and sales engagement tools is a plus\n\nYou are smart and work hard\n\nYou have an entrepreneurial spirit/experience with a strong growth mindset\n\nYou have a way with words and can write email copy and sequence campaigns that convert\n\nYou are adaptable and comfortable with a fast-paced environment\n\nYou are an active relationship builder who can collaborate with internal and external teams to consistently improve processes and communication workflows\n\nYou have worked for an HR or Fintech company, preferred\n\nYou've worked at a fast-growing startup, preferred\n\nYou have previously successfully worked in a remote & distributed team, preferred\n\nFully proficient in English + Dutch\n\nTotal Rewards\n\nOur workforce deserves fair and competitive pay that meets them where they are. With scalable benefits, rewards, and perks, our total rewards programs reflect our commitment to inclusivity and access for all.\n\nSome things you’ll enjoy\n\nStock grant opportunities dependent on your role, employment status and location\n\nAdditional perks and benefits based on your employment status and country\n\nThe flexibility of remote work, including optional WeWork access\n\nAt Deel, we’re an equal-opportunity employer that values diversity and positively encourage applications from suitably qualified and eligible candidates regardless of race, religion, sex, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, disability status, pregnancy or maternity or other applicable legally protected characteristics.\n\nUnless otherwise agreed, we will communicate with job applicants using Deel-specific emails, which include @deel.com and other acquired company emails like @payspace.com and @paygroup.com. You can view the most up-to-date job listings at Deel by visiting our careers page.\n\nDeel is an equal-opportunity employer and is committed to cultivating a diverse and inclusive workplace that reflects different abilities, backgrounds, beliefs, experiences, identities and perspectives.\n\nDeel will provide accommodations on request throughout the recruitment, selection and assessment process for applicants with disabilities. If you require accommodations, please inform our Talent Acquisition Team via this link and a team member will be in touch to ensure your equal participation. If you have difficulty accessing the form, please email at recruiting@deel.com.\n\nAs part of our hiring process, we primarily rely on interviews and role-related assessments. In limited cases, we may also consider informal background information relevant to the role, in line with our privacy and fairness obligations.\n\nThis application process does utilise Automated Employment Decision Tools (AEDT) and AI systems to assist in evaluating candidates based on experience level, technical skills and qualifications. As a fully remote company, we also utilise AI-powered deepfake and fraud detection technologies to verify the authenticity of candidate identities and interactions during assessments and interviews. This processing is conducted in compliance with applicable Data Protection, AI Governance and Labour Laws. We ensure human oversight is maintained in all final hiring decisions. Your personal data is not used to train AI models. For more information on how we process your personal data, please see our Privacy Policy.\n\nFor NYC Residents: In accordance with NYC Local Law 144, an independent bias audit has been conducted on AEDT; results are available at Ashby, Covey."}
